HEADWORD: Phlorizin
<hw>Phlor"i*zin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, <?/,
bark + <grk>"ri`za</grk> root.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A bitter
white crystalline glucoside extracted from the root bark of the apple,
pear, cherry, plum, etc.</def> <altsp>[Formerly also written
<asp>phloridzin</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

